TeachBooks.summary: There has been a significant Pull Request event, improving the directory structure and arguments, including the implementation of a 'start' sub-command. The directory structure has been modified to prevent incorrect directory usage and now supports a 'book' folder by default. Additionally, the 'teachbooks serve' command now has a 'start' sub-command to differentiate it from the 'stop' sub-command, and compatibility with existing functionality has been verified through thorough testing.

DivyeshVora79909/TeachBooks.summary: Recent activities include multiple Push Events that involve various updates, such as renaming directories, modifying the build strategy, adding version options, and enhancing the serve functionality. Moreover, improvements have been made to the build tests, and simple tests have been added for the CLI serve feature. The repository has also seen the merging of multiple pull requests, further refining the build and serve features, including the handling of temporary directories and the addition of a dev setup section.
